cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the development of an artificial immune system for detecting and responding to malicious code execution, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of system call analysis and behavioural information of running processes suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The proposed system also involves the integration of different types of information, which could be related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of a responsive system that adapts to new threats suggests the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE).
